column34:
Johnny Depp should be restored to his role of Captain Jack Sparrow after Amber Heard has defamed him, ruined his career and lied about her status as a victim. In fact, Mr. Depp is the victim as photographic evidence has shown, as well as audio where Ms. Heard admits to physically assaulting Mr. Depp. Ms. Heard has abused the judicial system as well as the #MeToo movement therefore casting a shadow on all actual victims of domestic abuse. She is an example of the worst sort of woman who cried abuse when she was, in fact, the abuser. Disney should not allow this fabrication of the truth to disrupt a beloved franchise that Mr. Depp helped build with his role in it. 

Disney should review their decision and renew Johnny's contract now that he has proven his innocence and withdraw the scrutiny they used against him when his ex-wife sought to destroy his entire life including his children's and other personal affairs. The fact that Ms. Heard has successfully ousted him from this role despite her lying and being the actual abuser is wrong and Disney should rectify this mistake.

column34:
Johnny Depp should be restored to his role of Captain Jack Sparrow after Amber Heard has defamed him, ruined his career and lied about her status as a victim. In fact, Mr. Depp is the victim as photographic evidence has shown, as well as audio where Ms. Heard admits to physically assaulting Mr. Depp. Ms. Heard has abused the judicial system as well as the #MeToo movement therefore casting a shadow on all actual victims of domestic abuse. She is an example of the worst sort of woman who cried abuse when she was, in fact, the abuser. Disney should not allow this fabrication of the truth to disrupt a beloved franchise that Mr. Depp helped build with his role in it. 

Disney should review their decision and renew Johnny's contract now that he has proven his innocence and withdraw the scrutiny they used against him when his ex-wife sought to destroy his entire life including his children's and other personal affairs. The fact that Ms. Heard has successfully ousted him from this role despite her lying and being the actual abuser is wrong and Disney should rectify this mistake.
